29/12/2002
BELGRADE, Yugoslavia -- By decree Friday (27 December), President Vojislav Kostunica appointed Branko Krga chief of staff of the Yugoslav Army. Serving as acting chief of staff since June, Krga was also promoted from lieutenant general to general. Krga spent most of his career in military intelligence. Also Friday, the Supreme Defence Council decided to declassify some secret documents related to war crimes indictees. The Council will send the files to the council on war crimes co-operation at the request of the UN tribunal in The Hague. (Tanjug, BBC, B92, FoNet - 27/12/02)
